
[1]cripple

   CRIPPLE, n. [G.] A lame person; primarily, one who creeps, halts or
   limps; one who has lost, or never enjoyed the use of his limbs. Acts
   14.

   The word may signify one who is partially or totally disabled from
   using his limbs.

   See the blind beggar dance, the cripple sing.

                              CRIPPLE, a. Lame.

                                CRIPPLE, v.t.

   1. To lame; to deprive of the use of the limbs, particularly of the
   legs and feet.

   2. To disable; to deprive of the power of exertion. We say, a fleet was
   crippled in the engagement.
